    summary:"Senolytic peptide — kills zombie cells (senescent cells). One of the most exciting aging reversal compounds.",
    description:`FOXO4-DRI is a modified retro-inverso peptide — a mirror-image version of a FOXO4 protein segment that is highly resistant to enzymatic degradation. Its target: senescent cells, also called "zombie cells."

Senescent cells are cells that have stopped dividing (usually due to DNA damage or telomere shortening) but refuse to undergo apoptosis (normal programmed death). Instead, they release a pro-inflammatory cocktail called SASP (Senescence-Associated Secretory Phenotype) that damages neighboring healthy tissue, drives chronic inflammation, and accelerates aging throughout the body.

FOXO4 is a protein that specifically protects senescent cells from death. In senescent cells (unlike healthy cells), FOXO4 moves into the nucleus and binds p53, blocking the apoptosis signal. FOXO4-DRI competitively disrupts this FOXO4-p53 interaction — removing the survival protection from senescent cells and allowing them to die naturally, while healthy cells (where this specific interaction doesn't occur the same way) are unharmed.

The landmark 2017 Cell paper showed: FOXO4-DRI treatment in aged mice restored physical fitness, improved fur regrowth, restored liver function, and induced hair regrowth in chemotherapy-induced alopecia. The results were visually dramatic.`,
